						               													<description>Lingo is a word game played with interlocking tiles.  Players take turns removing a single tile from the dispenser and placing it in the pool.  Any player can then call a word, using the letters in pool, or a combination of letters in the pool plus an already completed word.  If this word is unchallenged, the player claims the tiles and joins them as a word in his play area.  In this way, players can 'steal' a word from another player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the end of the game, players join all their words together.  The player with the longest 'word stick' is declared the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The dispenser is then used as a 'word breaker', as the sticks are fed into a slot and broken apart, ready for the next game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
